                <tr>				
					<th>The Chocolate Hills in the Philippines are popular for their unique and enchanting landscape, 
					 featuring over a thousand perfectly cone-shaped hills that turn brown during the dry season,
					 resembling a field of giant chocolate kisses.</th>
					<th>Davao City is popular for its vibrant culture, diverse attractions,
					 and being a gateway to the stunning landscapes of Mindanao, 
					 offering a mix of urban experiences, rich biodiversity, 
				     and the iconic Mount Apo, the highest peak in the Philippines.</th>
					<th>Baguio City, the "Summer Capital of the Philippines,"
					 is famous for its cool climate, scenic views, and cultural attractions, 
					 making it a popular destination for a refreshing escape and vibrant festivals.</th>		
